d operator is positive semidefinite\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:217:  clamped behavior and records that choice in the manifest\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:220:- coarse operators and transfer maps should be interpreted in the same inner\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:221:  product as the fine operator\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:223:## What the current bundle guarantees\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:225:`operator_bundle.v2` serializes:\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:227:- a dedicated fine operator archive with cotangent stiffness, lumped mass,\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:228:  symmetric mass-normalized operator form, and explicit supporting geometry\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:230:- anisotropy coefficients needed to reproduce the fine operator:\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:233:- a dedicated coarse operator archive with patch mass, Galerkin stiffness, the\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:234:  normalized coarse operator, and patch-local supporting arrays\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:235:- an explicit transfer-operator archive with physical-field restriction /\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:236:  prolongation, normalized-state transfer operators, and quality metrics\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:237:- an operator metadata sidecar that records the realized discretization,\\\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:238:  weighting scheme, frame convention, versioned `operator_assembly` config,\\\\ndocs/operator_qa.md:3:Milestone 6 is not finished when bundles merely serialize. Before follow-on\\\\ndocs/operator_qa.md:11:`scripts/06_operator_qa.py` is that workflow.\\\\ndocs/operator_qa.md:15:The report reads only local bundle artifacts that were already built by\\\\ndocs/operator_qa.md:18:- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_fine_operator.npz`\\\\ndocs/operator_qa.md:19:- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_coarse_operator.npz`\\\\ndocs/operator_qa.md:20:- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<r